{"id":14881454,"mediaExerciseId":"845384f4-e629-410f-8d83-25eee1173ea1","exerciseName":"2","chapterName":"14","chapterTitle":"Cost of Capital","groupId":612388,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":488,"solutions":[{"id":5981738,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"First, let's see the formula we will use to calculate the cost of equity capital which we denote with $C$\n\n$$\\begin{align*}\nC&=R+ B \\times (ER - R)\n\\end{align*}$$\n\nwhere the risk-free rate $R$ is $3.5\\%$, the beta $B$ is $1.07$ and the expected return $ER$ is $10\\%$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Now, let's do the calculation according to the formula\n\n$$\\begin{align*}\nC&=R+ B \\times (ER - R)\\\\[7pt]\n&=3.5\\% + 1.07 \\times (10\\%-3.5\\%)\\\\[7pt]\n&=0.035 + 1.07 \\times (0.1-0.035)\\\\[7pt]\n&=0.035 + 1.07 \\times 0.065\\\\[7pt]\n&=0.035+0.069\\\\[7pt]\n&=0.104\\\\[7pt]\n&=10.4\\%\n\\end{align*}$$\n\nTherefore, the cost of equity capital is $\\boxed{10.4\\%}$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"$\\boxed{10.4\\%}$","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":44,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/a22ed2e01698df268bbcbf54db428ddb/95a5a1690ba62e7e0aa6aa405cfcb310/lateximg_large.png","width":99},"regular":{"height":22,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/a22ed2e01698df268bbcbf54db428ddb/95a5a1690ba62e7e0aa6aa405cfcb310/lateximg.png","width":49}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":true,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"a2a99fd6-b36c-4196-809b-a8fcc54594fc","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Rando